workflow.name: Customer onboarding help requests (Typeform to Gmail & Sheets)
workflow.description:
## Description
Automatically capture customer onboarding help requests from Typeform, log them in Google Sheets, validate email addresses, and send a professional HTML welcome email via Gmail. Ensures smooth onboarding communication with audit-ready tracking and error handling. üìùüìß

## What This Template Does
- Monitors Typeform submissions for new onboarding help requests. üì•
- Logs all responses into Google Sheets with structured fields. üìä
- Validates email addresses to prevent errors. ‚úÖ
- Generates professional HTML welcome emails with company branding. üé®
- Sends onboarding emails directly via Gmail. üìß
- Handles missing or invalid emails with error logging. ‚ö†Ô∏è

## Key Benefits
- Streamlines customer onboarding request handling. ‚è±Ô∏è
- Creates a centralized log for analytics and audits. üßæ
- Improves customer experience with branded email communication. üí°
- Reduces manual effort in follow-up and data entry. üîÑ
- Ensures reliable handling of incomplete or invalid submissions. üõ°Ô∏è

## Features
- Typeform trigger for new form submissions. üìù
- Automatic Google Sheets logging of customer details. üìà
- Conditional email validation before sending. üîç
- Dynamic HTML email generation with customer details. üé®
- Automated Gmail delivery of welcome emails. üìß
- Error handling node for missing/invalid email submissions. üö®

## Requirements
- n8n instance (cloud or self-hosted).
- Typeform API credentials with webhook permissions.
- Google Sheets OAuth2 credentials with spreadsheet write access.
- Gmail OAuth2 credentials with send email permissions.
- Pre-configured Google Sheet for onboarding request tracking.

## Target Audience
- Customer success and onboarding teams. üë©‚Äçüíª
- SaaS startups managing onboarding inquiries. üöÄ
- Support teams handling product/service onboarding. üõ†Ô∏è
- SMBs looking for efficient onboarding automation. üè¢
- Remote teams needing structured onboarding workflows. üåê

### Step-by-Step Setup Instructions
- Connect Typeform, Google Sheets, and Gmail credentials in n8n. üîë
- Insert your Typeform form ID in the trigger node. üìù
- Replace the Google Sheet ID with your tracking sheet. üìä
- Map form fields to spreadsheet columns (ensure headers match). üîó
- Customize email HTML template with branding and company info. üé®
- Update sender email in the Gmail node. üìß
- Test the workflow with a sample form submission. ‚úÖ

parameters.content:
üéØ **STEP 1: Form Capture**

Triggers when someone submits your Typeform with onboarding help request.

**Setup:**
- Add your Typeform ID
- Connect Typeform credentials
- Webhook automatically configured

üìä **STEP 2: Data Logging**

Appends all form data to Google Sheets for tracking and analytics.

**Setup:**
- Replace with your Sheet ID
- Map form fields to columns
- Ensure headers match

‚úÖ **STEP 3: Email Validation**

Checks if valid email exists before sending welcome message.

**Logic:**
- TRUE: Proceed to email generation
- FALSE: Log error and skip email

üé® **STEP 4: Email Template**

Generates professional HTML email with:
- Company branding
- Customer details
- Next steps
- Contact information

**Customize:**
- Colors and styling
- Company information
- Action items

üìß **STEP 5: Send Email**

Delivers welcome email using Gmail.

**Important:**
- Update sender email address
- Test with internal emails first
- Monitor delivery rates

‚ö†Ô∏è **Error Handler**

Logs submissions without valid email addresses for manual follow-up.

**Use case:**
- Incomplete form submissions
- Invalid email formats
- Manual review needed

options.systemMessage:
=You are an AI assistant that processes raw form submissions from surveys or onboarding forms. 
Your job is to read all the answers and generate a structured, professional summary. 

Rules:
- Always produce output as clean JSON (no free text).
- Keep "summary" concise (2‚Äì3 sentences).
- In "insights", list key observations or potential issues as bullet points (max 5).
- In "callToAction", give one short, actionable recommendation for the internal team.
- If answers are irrelevant, empty, or missing, clearly state "Not provided" instead of skipping.
- Do not repeat raw text verbatim; rephrase into professional insights.

parameters.content:
üìå **Create ClickUp Task**

Automatically creates a task in ClickUp for every valid submission.

**Setup:**
- Task name = tutorial completed
- Assignee = customer name (or adjust to team member)

üìä **Save Task Data**

Appends or updates ClickUp task details into a second Google Sheet.

**Purpose:**
- Maintain enriched task dataset
- Easy reporting on support/onboarding requests

ü§ñ **AI Summarizer**

Reads full form submission and produces a clean structured JSON with:
- Summary (2‚Äì3 sentences)
- Insights (bullet points)
- Call To Action (one next step)

Ensures raw text is turned into actionable insights.

üõ†Ô∏è **Format ClickUp Data**

Cleans and structures task data from ClickUp before logging it into Google Sheets.

**Includes:**
- Dates (created, due, closed)
- Assignees, watchers, tags
- Priority, status, custom fields
- Task URL and metadata

üß† **Language Model**

Powers the AI Agent by providing GPT-4o capabilities from Azure OpenAI.

**Setup:**
- Connected with your Azure credentials
- Model: gpt-4o

üóÇÔ∏è **Conversation Memory**

Provides short-term memory to the AI Agent for context handling.

**Config:**
- Keeps last 7 turns
- Session key = json_review

üì¶ **Structured Parser**

Validates and enforces AI output into the required JSON format.

**Schema:**
- summary: string
- insights: array of strings
- callToAction: string

üí¨ **Slack Notification**

Posts AI-generated summary, insights, and action items to a Slack channel.

**Setup:**
- Channel: reply-needed
- Format: summary + insights + call to action

data.details: The Function node allows you to execute JavaScript in your workflow. Unlike the Function Item node, this node does not operate on incoming node data per-item. Instead, you must iterate over multiple items of incoming data yourself. This can be useful if you're performing data transformation where you want to manipulate the number of items being outputted by the node (i.e. 1 item is inputted in with nested object, 10 items are outputted without any nested objects)

data.details:
The IF node can be used to implement binary conditional logic in your workflow. You can set up one-to-many conditions to evaluate each item of data being inputted into the node. That data will either evaluate to TRUE or FALSE and route out of the node accordingly.

This node has multiple types of conditions: Bool, String, Number, and Date & Time.
